@bcherny Claude Code Feature request: Hook to modify tool output before it gets back to the model.
At our company, we have a small set of files/code that must not leave the premises, even to Claude Code. We do our best with PreToolUse to stop any obvious attempts to read blacklisted files, but there are many innocuous-looking commands that might return blacklisted code (i.e. grep, git, etc.)
It would be great to have a script that could scan any tool output for blacklisted code and strip it out.
